   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# `pseudo_electrostatic_packing`\n",
    "This is a form of random sequential addition (`rsa`) where spheres are inserted as close to the specified points as possible without overlapping."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "909f268e",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:27.863111Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:27.862856Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:30.155044Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:30.154430Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import porespy as ps\n",
    "import inspect"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7fab9c9a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `im`\n",
    "The image into which the spheres should be inserted.  Spheres will be inserted into the ``True`` locations, as if these  indicate void space. If `sites` is not specified, then the spheres will be clustered around the center of the image."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "6549258e",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:30.167734Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:30.167486Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:31.467695Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:31.467065Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "im = ~ps.generators.borders(shape=[200, 200], mode='faces')\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_electrostatic_packing(im=im, r=10, maxiter=35)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(im, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"input im\")\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(packing, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"spheres\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "085c6e40",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `sites`\n",
    "A boolean array with ``True`` values indicating the points where spheres are 'electrostatically' drawn to.  If not given, the function performs a distance transform of the image and uses all peaks."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "4e96524a",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:31.470145Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:31.469932Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:31.608711Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:31.608166Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sites = ps.generators.borders(shape=[200, 200], mode='corners', thickness=30)\n",
    "im = np.ones_like(sites, dtype=bool)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_electrostatic_packing(im=im, sites=sites, r=8, maxiter=50)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(sites, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"sites\")\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(packing, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"output\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "74a2651a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `r`\n",
    "The radius of the spheres to add:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "bb0a85c7",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:31.611263Z",

      "image/png": "",

   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "r = 5\n",
    "im = ~ps.generators.borders(shape=[151, 151], mode='faces')\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_electrostatic_packing(im=im, r=r)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(packing, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",

   ]

   "id": "106496c6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `clearance`\n",
    "The spheres can be forced to have some spacing between them by setting ``clearance > 0``, or they can overlap if ``clearance < 0``:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "8d69dc9a",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {

   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "clearance=-1\n",
    "im = ~ps.generators.borders(shape=[151, 151], mode='faces')\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_electrostatic_packing(im=im, r=r, clearance=clearance)\n",

    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(f'clearance: {clearance}')\n",

    "clearance=5\n",
    "im = ~ps.generators.borders(shape=[151, 151], mode='faces')\n",

    "ax[1].imshow(packing, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(f'clearance: {clearance}');"
   ]
  },
  {

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `protrusion` \n",
    "One of the uses of this function is to insert spheres like carbon particles into a matrix, like polymer.  In these cases it may be desirable to have the spheres protrude slightly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "932d6982",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:31.961172Z",

    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [

      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[10, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "protrusion = -2\n",
    "im = ~ps.generators.borders(shape=[151, 151], mode='faces', thickness=20)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_electrostatic_packing(im=im, r=10, protrusion=protrusion)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(packing + 0.5*im, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(f\"protrusion: {protrusion}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "protrusion = 8\n",
    "im = ~ps.generators.borders(shape=[151, 151], mode='faces', thickness=20)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_electrostatic_packing(im=im, r=10, protrusion=protrusion)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(packing + 0.5*im, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(f\"protrusion: {protrusion}\");"
   ]
  },
